Name: Netherlands Bank Discount Rate on Bills of Exchange
Periodicity:
Annual From Dec 1596 To Jan 1814
Monthly From Feb 1814 To Jan 1870
Weekly From Jan 1870 To Aug 1914
Monthly From Aug 1914 To Jun 1985
Daily From Jul 1985 To Dec 1993
Metadata:
Sources: William Sumner (ed.), A History of Banking, NY: Journal of Commerce, 1896, Vol. IV, pp. 241, 309, (1814-1894) The Economist (1894-1918), League of Nations (1919-45), Netherlands Bank, Quarterly Bulletin and Central Bureau of Statistics, Maandschrift (1946-)
Data from 1596 to 1620 is the annual average interest rate on IOUs issued by Amsterdam merchants from Oscar Gelderblom and Joost Joncker, Completing a Financial Revolution: The Finance of Dutch East India Trade and the Rise of the Amsterdam Capital Market, 1595-1612, Journal of Economic History, 64:3 (September 2004)
